"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104etu1719376772254.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/etu1719376772254.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/etu1719376772254.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xgj1665702600898\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__compute__209058\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Assigns the value of an expression to a field, variable, or function.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d69368e1_d69369e1_d69370e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104etu1719376772254_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__codeblock_hg3_ptz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">{compute} Target{/init} = Expression</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__p_d69374e1_d69375e1_d69376e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">JOBSTATUS/init = \"Employed\"</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d45457e1_d45458e1_d45459e1_d45460e1_d45461e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e71\">\n                       \n Qualifiers\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Qualifiers</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1__entry__1\">\n Qualifier\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">compute</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1__entry__2\">\n Computes the value of <var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var> and assigns it to <var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>. In practice, the statement is omitted, leaving only the assignment operator.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/init</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6068e1_d6069e1_d6070e1__entry__2\">\n Sets the value of the target field in a non-database occurrence without changing the status of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldmod</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occdbmod</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancemod</span>, or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancedbmod</span>.\n <p class=\"p\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/init</span> switch is useful when you are assigning a retrieve profile for an empty entity or initializing values in a new occurrence.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">This switch has no effect once a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve</span> has been completed.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d45462e1_d45463e1_d45464e1_d45465e1_d45466e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e169\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__3\">\n Name of a field, variable, or function. (Not all functions can serve as the target of an assignment.)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xgj1665702600898__table_d6071e1_d6072e1_d6073e1__entry__3\">\n Expression made up of operators and parentheses used to combine elements of the ProcScript language, that is, constants, fields, variables, and functions.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d45467e1_d45468e1_d45469e1_d45470e1_d45471e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e237\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__p_d69386e1_d69387e1_d69388e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">=</span> statement does not affect <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d45472e1_d45473e1_d45474e1_d45475e1_d45476e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e253\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d45477e1_d45478e1_d45479e1_d45480e1_d45481e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e262\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__p_d69398e1_d69399e1_d69400e1\">In an assignment statement, reading from left to right, the first equals sign (=) is the assignment operator. If more than one equals sign occurs, the rest are interpreted as relational operators. For example, in the following figure, the Boolean result of the expression <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">x=\"A\"</span> is assigned to vBool:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__fig_d69401e1_d69402e1_d69403e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Multiple equals signs in a compute statement</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Multiple equals signs in a compute statement\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/equals.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31685e1_d31686e1_d31687e1\">Assignment operator\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31688e1_d31689e1_d31690e1\">Relational operator\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31691e1_d31692e1_d31693e1\">Boolean value\n </li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__note_w1339ab1b7c13b9_w1340ab1b7c13_w1341ab1b7_w1342ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> In self-contained services and reports, global variables and some ProcScript functions cannot be used in the expression, nor as the target of the assignment.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__p_d69407e1_d69408e1_d69409e1\">The value of <var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var> is\n            implicitly converted to the data type associated with <var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>. For\n            more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hju1665702578520.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hju1665702578520.html\" title=\"When assigning, comparing, and evaluating data in variables, fields, parameters, and expressions, it is possible for mismatches in data type to occur. In such cases, Uniface does not generate an error, but implicitly converts the data type from its source type to the target type.\">Type Conversion</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__topic_d45482e1_d45483e1_d45484e1_d45485e1_d45486e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e318\">\n                       Compound Operators</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__p_d69413e1_d69414e1_d69415e1\">\n            \n            Compound operators combine the assignment operator (<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>) with an\n\t\tarithmetic operator. They provide a shorthand notation when performing an arithmetic calculation on\n\t\tthe value of a field or variable and assigning the result to the same field or variable. For\n\t\texample:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31694e1_d31695e1_d31696e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">A += 1</code> is equal to <code class=\"ph codeph\">A\n\t\t\t = A + 1</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31697e1_d31698e1_d31699e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">A -= 1</code> is equal to <code class=\"ph codeph\">A\n\t\t\t = A - 1</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31700e1_d31701e1_d31702e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">A *= 2</code> is equal to <code class=\"ph codeph\">A\n\t\t\t = A * 2 </code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31703e1_d31704e1_d31705e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">A /= 3</code> is equal to <code class=\"ph codeph\">A\n\t\t\t = A / 3</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__li_d31706e1_d31707e1_d31708e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">A %= 10</code> is equal to <code class=\"ph codeph\">A\n\t\t\t = A % 10</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__section_hmn_qg1_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e382\">Example: = </h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows the use of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">compute</code>\n            statement:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__pre_cqw_rg1_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger loseFocus\n TOTPRICE = (QUANTITY * PRICE)\n $1 = CUSTNAME\n $2 = \"price modified\"\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__section_hxz_ng1_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537543e397\">Example: Setting a Retrieve Profile Using /init</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example uses the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/init</span> switch to set a\n            retrieve profile in the exec operation of a component.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"xgj1665702600898__pre_cgw_4g1_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation exec\n GENDER/init = \"M\"\n JOB/init = \"RETIRED\"\n retrieve\nend; exec</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjy1665702601052.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldmod</a><p>Return the modification status of a field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/atw1665702600492.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$instancemod</a><p>Return or set the modification status of data in the current component instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eai1665702600334.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occmod</a><p>Return the modification status of an occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/len1665702601301.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$instancedbmod</a><p>Return the modification status of database fields in the current component instance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7420486\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7420486\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "= (compute) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Assigns the value of an expression to a field, variable, or function. Explain this code {compute} Target{/init} = Expression Copy Example: JOBSTATUS/init = \"Employed\" Qualifiers Table 1. Qualifiers Qualifier Description compute Computes the value of Expression and assigns it to Target . In practice, the statement is omitted, leaving only the assignment operator. /init Sets the value of the target field in a non-database occurrence without changing the status of $fieldmod , $occmod , $occdbmod , $formmod , $formdbmod , $instancemod , or $instancedbmod . The /init switch is useful when you are assigning a retrieve profile for an empty entity or initializing values in a new occurrence. This switch has no effect once a retrieve has been completed. Parameters Table 2. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description Target String Name of a field, variable, or function. (Not all functions can serve as the target of an assignment.) Expression Expression made up of operators and parentheses used to combine elements of the ProcScript language, that is, constants, fields, variables, and functions. Return Values The = statement does not affect $status . Use Allowed in all component types. Description In an assignment statement, reading from left to right, the first equals sign (=) is the assignment operator. If more than one equals sign occurs, the rest are interpreted as relational operators. For example, in the following figure, the Boolean result of the expression x=\"A\" is assigned to vBool: Figure 1. Multiple equals signs in a compute statement Assignment operator Relational operator Boolean value Note: In self-contained services and reports, global variables and some ProcScript functions cannot be used in the expression, nor as the target of the assignment. The value of Expression is implicitly converted to the data type associated with Target . For more information, see Type Conversion . Compound Operators Compound operators combine the assignment operator ( = ) with an arithmetic operator. They provide a shorthand notation when performing an arithmetic calculation on the value of a field or variable and assigning the result to the same field or variable. For example: A += 1 is equal to A = A + 1 A -= 1 is equal to A = A - 1 A *= 2 is equal to A = A * 2 A /= 3 is equal to A = A / 3 A %= 10 is equal to A = A % 10 Example: = The following example shows the use of the compute statement: trigger loseFocus TOTPRICE = (QUANTITY * PRICE) $1 = CUSTNAME $2 = \"price modified\" end Copy Example: Setting a Retrieve Profile Using /init The following example uses the /init switch to set a retrieve profile in the exec operation of a component. operation exec GENDER/init = \"M\" JOB/init = \"RETIRED\" retrieve end; exec Copy Related Links $fieldmod Return the modification status of a field. $instancemod Return or set the modification status of data in the current component instance. $occmod Return the modification status of an occurrence. $instancedbmod Return the modification status of database fields in the current component instance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}